<div class="section">
    <h1>Connecting to the VPN</h1>
    <p>If you are trying to connect from Linux, <a href="http://i.imgur.com/bEI8Ugr.png">please click here</a></p>
    <ol>
        <li><span>Download the OpenVPN desktop client <a href="http://swupdate.openvpn.net/downloads/openvpn-client.msi">here</a></span></li>
        <li><span>Install the program, making sure you click yes if it asks you to install network drivers</span></li>
        <li><span>Start the OpenVPN client</li>
        <li><span>Download the config file from <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/24279633/lsucs.ovpn">here</a></span></li>
        <li><span>On the right of where it says 'Connection Profiles', click the '+' symbol</span></li>
        <li><span>Check the 'Local File' box, then click the 'Import' button</span></li>
        <li><span>It will prompt you to find a file. Navigate to where you downloaded the config file and select it (lsucs.ovpn)</span></li>
        <li><span>Make sure 'Completely trust this profile' is checked, then click 'Save'</span></li>
        <li><span>Click the lsucs profile square at the bottom of the OpenVPN window. It should ask you for your username and password</span></li>
        <li><span>Enter your login details and click ok. If entered correctly, OpenVPN will load config, assign an IP and tell you it is connected</span></li>
        <li><span>You can verify it is connected by opening command prompt and typing 'ping 10.8.0.1'. If it goes through, you are connected. If it is timed out, see the FAQ</span></li>
    </ol>
</div>

